<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-039-328 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 367 603</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Oct 7 1991 v8 n40 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SyQuest to unveil 2.5-inch removable drive. (SyQuest TechnologySQ2542A)(brief article) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sullivan, Kristina B.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   SyQuest Technology Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   SyQuest Technology SQ2542A (Removable hard disk drive) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Disk drivesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Kristina B. SullivanandM;Momentarily bypassing the 3-1/2-inch form factor, SyQuest Technology thisweek will introduce a 2-1/2-inch removable-cartridge hard-disk drive designedfor laptop PCs.andP;  The 42.8M-byte SQ2542A, available now in sample quantitiesand due in volume by mid-1992, gives laptop users unlimited storagecapabilities, said Joel Levine, vice president of marketing for SyQuest inFremont, Calif.andP;  &quot;With notebooks, we have been so concerned about power,weight and size that we as an industry sacrificed capacity.&quot;andM;The 2-1/2-inch drive will be offered to OEMs for $250.andP;  Each 42.8M-bytecartridge is expected to sell for $60, Levine said.andP;  SyQuest is also planninga family of 3-1/2-inch removable-cartridge hard-disk drives, he said.andM;The SQ2542A includes a feature that lets users save power by selecting from arange of seek rates.andP;  Notebook makers can implement this feature as auser-controlled software command or as an automatic function.andM;SyQuest can be reached at (510) 226-4000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>